1.DVWA was installed on the Metasploitable2 virtual machine.
2.DVWA security level was set to LOW.
3.The target IP address was identified using ip a.
4.The DVWA web application was accessed from Kali Linux.
5.Burp Suite was configured with Firefox to intercept and modify requests.
6.Manual SQL Injection testing was performed on input parameters.
7.Automated SQL Injection testing was carried out using sqlmap.
8.Reflected XSS vulnerability was tested using crafted payloads.
9.Authentication mechanisms were reviewed for improper access controls.
10.Brute force attacks were performed to test lack of rate-limiting and account lockout protections.
11.Command Injection testing was performed by injecting system commands into vulnerable input fields (ping parameter).
12.Successful command execution was verified through ping responses.
13.All findings were documented with screenshots and proof of exploitation.
